# Using React Context API

- I investigated further on the use cases of React Ccontext APIs.
- They help to avoid the nebulous task of props drilling
- They help us to share our state between different components that are wrapped inside the created context
- Here is a link to a very simple application of context API
- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sP7ANcTpJr8
- I also checked out an article for better understanding:https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/react-context-for-beginners/
